== [[Matis Weinberg]] article ==

Eyes and comments are needed on the {{Article|Matis Weinberg}} article with regard to [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Matis_Weinberg&diff=605409818&oldid=605409755 this controversy matter]. There is back and forth reverting at that article among IPs when it comes that material. Yes, [[User:Josve05a|Josve05a]] and I have reverted at that article, restoring the material, but maybe we should not have. This is my first time truly looking at the controversy material. [[User:Flyer22|Flyer22]] ([[User talk:Flyer22|talk]]) 05:50, 23 April 2014 (UTC)

My [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Matis_Weinberg&diff=605409755&oldid=605409409 removing the material] after seeing a "possible BLP issue or vandalism" tag before restoring it minutes ago is what led me to look closer. [[User:Flyer22|Flyer22]] ([[User talk:Flyer22|talk]]) 05:55, 23 April 2014 (UTC)
:I see this article as highly problematic and encourage other editors to take a close look. The subject is a rabbi and educator who has repeatedly been accused of sexual improprieties, which he has denied vigorously. Charges before a bet din (rabbinical court) were dropped and I don't think he has been arrested or convicted by the justice system. Since his notability is based mostly on material that is controversial from the BLP policy point of view, deletion may be the best solution. What do others think? [[User:Cullen328|'''<font color="green">Cullen</font>'''<sup><font color="purple">328</font></sup>]] [[User talk:Cullen328|<font color="blue">''Let's discuss it''</font>]] 17:49, 26 April 2014 (UTC)
::That sounds like a plan very much in keeping with the wisdom of the [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_abuse_cases_in_Brooklyn%27s_Haredi_community#Relationship_with_law_enforcement community leaders in question].  They're surely quite wise, so we can follow their lead without thinking about it too much ourselves.  [[User:Nomoskedasticity|Nomoskedasticity]] ([[User talk:Nomoskedasticity|talk]]) 18:17, 26 April 2014 (UTC)
:::Please note, {{U|Nomoskedasticity}}, that I asked for ideas from other editors about how to deal with what I see as the serious BLP issues here. I have not nominated the article for deletion though I don't like what I see. I don't do the bidding of Orthodox rabbis here, as a brief glance at my edit history will show. I am aware, as well, of the problems with secretiveness among Haredi Jews. But Wikipedia is not a forum to right great wrongs, and our BLP policy applies to all, including ultra-Orthodox rabbis. How do ''you'' think we should deal with such unproven allegations? [[User:Cullen328|'''<font color="green">Cullen</font>'''<sup><font color="purple">328</font></sup>]] [[User talk:Cullen328|<font color="blue">''Let's discuss it''</font>]] 03:00, 28 April 2014 (UTC)

