== Peter Rees (producer) ==

There's a disagreement between some editors and the apparent subject of the article going on on {{la|Peter Rees (producer)}}. The editors want to include a statement that the subject, a TV producer, had to leave a TV show after a prsenter received a severe electric shock. The source cited is a YouTube clip of the prsenter giving an account. Insufficient source for this acusation, in my view. But in any case, the prsenter doesn't allege a causal link in the clip anyway. The other editors seem to be more interested in COI allegations than BLP so more eyes on this article would be a good idea. [[User:DeCausa|DeCausa]] ([[User talk:DeCausa|talk]]) 08:44, 2 May 2014 (UTC)
:I'm sorry but this is not at all true. The content that DeCausa refers to was added in 2013 by an editor whose only ever edits to Wikipedia were [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Peter_Rees_%28producer%29&diff=561254580&oldid=547748838 these edits] to the article. Nobody else has argued that the content be included in the article. The restoration of the edits have been the natural result of an editor claiming to be the subject adding original research and inappropriate claims about the hosts of [[MythBusters]] to the article,[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Peter_Rees_%28producer%29&diff=603398164&oldid=591548342] and then completely destroying the article with a subsequent edit.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Peter_Rees_%28producer%29&diff=next&oldid=606321581] When the edits were reverted, the claim was restored to the article in the process of reversion. The offending claim has been removed by DeCausa,[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Peter_Rees_%28producer%29&diff=606741564&oldid=606738372] who has explained his action on the talk page,[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Talk%3APeter_Rees_%28producer%29&diff=606741860&oldid=606737692] and whose actions I supported.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Talk:Peter_Rees_%28producer%29&diff=next&oldid=606741860] The issue now is that of COI and legal threats by the editor, who has yet to prove that is who he says he is. --[[User:AussieLegend|'''<span style="color:green;">Aussie</span><span style="color:gold;">Legend</span>''']] ([[User talk:AussieLegend#top|<big>✉</big>]]) 12:06, 2 May 2014 (UTC)

::It's not untrue at all. The BLP breach was restored three times over two days. The last time it was restored the edit ''only'' included a restoration of the BLP breach and no other material. [[User:DeCausa|DeCausa]] ([[User talk:DeCausa|talk]]) 17:03, 2 May 2014 (UTC)

== [[Donald Sterling]]  accusations of a third party being a Prostitute ==

[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Donald_Sterling&diff=606825770&oldid=606823398]   shows a blanket revert of material which includes what I consider to be exceedingly serious BLP violations -- including accusations that another person is a prostitute, and a third was a "mistress".    BTW, there is no way that Castro is "notable" or in any way subject to any exception from strict compliance with the policy. 

It also contains speculation about criminal intent in a real estate project,  etc.


I consider such re-insertion of fairly contentious material (saying a person committed felonies is contentious IMHO) is intolerable.

I was "warned" on this by a person who wrote:

::'' '''All that is not mandated to be deleted can be included, and all that is allowed to be included should not be deleted'''; BLP therefore assures that there should be '''no deletion of contentious material with a reliable source'''. Edit summaries should not include contentiousness as a sole rationale.''

Which I am either bemused by or affronted by.   The idea that '''all that is not forbidden is required''' is Orwellian enough, but  how one can stretch that to calling another person a "prostitute" and think it does not violate [[WP:BLP]] is quite beyond my ken.   By the way, the sources refer to "allegation" and I consider "allegations" of criminal acts to not be worth the paper they are printed on for statements in any BLP.  Cheers. [[User:Collect|Collect]] ([[User talk:Collect|talk]]) 00:52, 3 May 2014 (UTC)

