== [[Jaiyah Saelua]] ==

[[Jaiyah Saelua]] is an international footballer who identifies as a [[fa'afafine]]. All the press items which involve interviewing the subject make it clear that [[fa'afafine]] is the primary identification [http://www.smh.com.au/sport/football/finally-making-history-for-all-the-right-reasons-20111125-1nz0s.html]. In some, teammates are quoted using female pronouns for the subject [http://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=11249328].  They play in the [[FIFA]] men's league.  The article identified the subject as [[transgender]] and the talk page as a [[trans women]]. As far as I can see [[fa'afafine]] should be used in both of these places. The fact that the western media is translating this non-western gender into western concepts in order to explain things to the readers is of no concern when it comes to [[WP:MOSIDENTITY]].

